olio based on your risk tolerance and investment goals. They are a hands-off way to manage your assets when you don’t have time or don’t want the pressure of doing it yourself. Most robo-advisors don’t have minimum investments, but for those that do, $500 is enough to start an account. Most brokers have their own robo-advisor offerings, or you can use robo-advisors like <a href=\"https://www.wealthfront.com/\">Wealthfront</a> or <a href=\"https://www.betterment.com/\">Betterment</a>.","<strong>Online Stock Trading vs Stock Brokers </strong>","Fees and commissions are a top concern for any investor. Over time, trading expenses can add up, meaning less money in your account. In the last year, the online stock trading brokers we reviewed have reduced their commissions to between $2.95 and $6.95 per trade. A regular broker’s commission can range from $19.99 to $44.99 per transaction, and it’s easy to see why online trading has become so popular. At 20 trades per year, broker-assisted trading alone can add up to about $400 to $900 per year. So, online stock broking is a lower investment. However, engaging a regular stock broker will give you access to expert advice and years of experience. ","<strong>What are Robo-advisors?</strong>","Robo-advisors are a low cost, automated investment platforms. These robo-advisors are recommended for casual investors that do not have a lot of free time to manage their trading portfolio. Robo-investors use algorithms to manage your stock trading portfolio so less confident stock traders do not have to pick all the individual investments. Not all online stock trading platforms will have the option of robo-advisors. These accounts typically invest in ETFs and mutual funds.","<strong>How do robo-advisors work?</strong>","A robo advisor will ask you a set of questions about your income, risk tolerance, and investment goals. Based on your answers, the robo-advisor uses an algorithm to suggest investments, create a diversified portfolio and manage it. Some of these automated stock trading platforms also rebalance your portfolio and use tax harvesting to lower your liability to the IRS. ","<strong>Why use a robo-investor? </strong>","The advantages of a robo investor include: "]},"id":"676fb323-e763-4900-9fc8-8f77763dffc9","type":"text"},{"data":{"items":["<strong>Low Fee Stock Trading:</strong> The automated approach allows for a more competitive cost as all the work is done by software. ","<strong>Conflict Free: </strong>Human stock brokers sometimes feel pressured to sell a specific product to clients as they have financial deals with companies. A robo-investor will not act in it’s own best interest over yours. ","<strong>Lower Minimum Investment:</strong> The minimum investment needed for a robo-investor is as low as $500. This means it is a lower commitment to invest than conventional financial advisors. ","<strong>Always Available:</strong> Robo-investors are always there when you need them, and you don’t have to wait on line listening to hold music to get the help you need."],"type":"ul"},"id":"7a259029-8457-4447-995d-24722b76a8d6","type":"list"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["<strong>What to look for in an online stock trading platform </strong>","To ensure you online stock broker is safe and trustworthy there are a number of official and professional regulations and trust that they should belong to.  When searching for a stock exchange platform, the professional bodies they belong to should be noted very clearly in an easy to find location. Ensure that they are members of the <a href=\"https://www.sipc.org/list-of-members/\">Securities Investor Protection Corporation (SIPC)</a> and the <a href=\"https://brokercheck.finra.org/\">Financial Industry Regulatory Authority</a>. ","If the broker is offering additional services such as a checking or savings accounts they should also be fully covered by the <a href=\"https://www.investopedia.com/terms/f/fdic.asp\">Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC)</a>